Package de.happybavarian07.coolstufflib.languagemanager.expressionengine

Klasse Interpreter

java.lang.Object
de.happybavarian07.coolstufflib.languagemanager.expressionengine.Interpreter
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Parser.Expression.Visitor<Object>
public class Interpreter extends Object implements Parser.Expression.Visitor<Object>
The interpreter evaluates parsed expressions and computes their values.

This class implements the Visitor pattern to traverse the expression tree produced by the Parser and computes a result value. It supports mathematical operations, logical operations, variable references, and function calls.

The interpreter maintains internal state in the form of variables and registered functions that can be referenced during expression evaluation.

    • interpret

      public Object interpret(Parser.Expression expression)
      Evaluates the given expression and returns its result.

      This is the main entry point for expression evaluation. It handles any runtime errors that may occur during evaluation and wraps them with additional context.

      Parameter:
      expression - The expression to evaluate
      Gibt zurück:
      The result of evaluating the expression
      Löst aus:
      RuntimeException - if an error occurs during evaluation

    • getVariable

      public Object getVariable(String name)
      Retrieves a variable by name and decrements its remaining uses. If the variable has no remaining uses, it is removed from the map.
      Parameter:
      name - The name of the variable to retrieve.
      Gibt zurück:
      The value of the variable, or null if it does not exist or has no remaining uses.

    • peekVariable

      public Object peekVariable(String name)
      Peeks at a variable's value without decrementing its uses. This is useful for checking the value without modifying its state.
      Parameter:
      name - The name of the variable to peek at.
      Gibt zurück:
      The value of the variable, or null if it does not exist.
